    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that sounds like a lot of theory, but in the real world, don't the economists mostly agree that free trade is just better for growth? it feels like protectionism is just an outdated idea that ignores how much more efficient global supply chains are. isn't the consensus basically that tariffs are just bad policy?",
