      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The prevailing consensus among mainstream economists is that free trade is superior for global growth and efficiency. Global supply chains are incredibly efficient because they allow nations to specialize in what they do best, driving down costs for consumers worldwide. Protectionism, by contrast, forces inefficient domestic industries to survive, which ultimately wastes resources and slows overall economic dynamism. Therefore, the academic consensus strongly favors open markets over restrictive tariffs.",
